125th Street, west side, north from and across 15th Avenue. The house at the N.W. corner of the intersection was owned by H. Funke in 1891, and so did the rest of the land extending beyond the water tank. The latter is at the N.W. corner of 14th Avenue. 125th Street was formerly named North 16th Street.
P. L. Sperr  March 16, 1932
